Class Cell

java.lang.Object
  Cell
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Cell
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A graph representation of one slice of a single cell. This objects contains references to its Vertex objects.

Author:
Michael Gelbart

Constructor Detail

Cell

public Cell(Cell toCopy)
Create a copy of the Cell and thus all of its Vertices. This is not especially useful, because we probably don't want to copy all the Vertices given that they are shared by other cells.

Cell

public Cell(int[] centroid,
            Vertex[] inputVertices,
            CellGraph parent)
Create a new Cell with coordinates (y,x) and vertices inputVerts. The constructor automatically sorts the Vertices into clockwise order.

Cell

public Cell(Vertex[] vertices,
            CellGraph parent)
Alternate constructor that assumes the vertices are already sorted.
